                                <td>0.5</td>
                                <td>1</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody></table>
                    </div>
                </figure>
                <p>Step 1 is to square this matrix =E2=80=93 i.e. multiply =
the matrix by itself =E2=80=93 which involves calculating its =E2=80=9Cdot =
products=E2=80=9D.</p>
                <p>Start by multiplying each number in the =E2=80=9Ccamera=
=E2=80=9D <em>row</em> by the corresponding number in the =E2=80=9Ccamera=
=E2=80=9D <em>column</em> and sum the products: (1 =C3=97 1) + (0.2 =C3=97 =
5) + (3 =C3=97 0.33=CC=87=CC=87) + (4 =C3=97 0.25) =3D 4. This first =E2=80=
=9Cdot product=E2=80=9D appears in the top-left cell of the squared matrix =
below. The other 15 dot products are calculated analogously.</p>
                <p>Thus, next multiply each number in the =E2=80=9Ccamera=
=E2=80=9D <em>row</em> as above but this time by the corresponding number i=
n the =E2=80=9Cstorage=E2=80=9D <em>column</em>, and again sum the products=
 (=3D 1.305); and then multiply the =E2=80=9Ccamera=E2=80=9D row by the =E2=
=80=9Clooks=E2=80=9D column and sum the products (9.800), and, finally, mul=
tiply the =E2=80=9Ccamera=E2=80=9D row by the =E2=80=9Cprice=E2=80=9D colum=
n and sum the products (15.400). Then, move down to the =E2=80=9Cstorage=E2=
=80=9D row and repeat the multiplications/summations outlined above for eac=
h of the columns; and then for the =E2=80=9Clooks=E2=80=9D row; and, finall=
y, the =E2=80=9Cprice=E2=80=9D row.</p>
                <aside class=3D"cta-excel-download container">
                    <a download=3D"" href=3D"https://www.1000minds.com/libr=
