r tables below. In each table, columns 2-4 comprise the squared pairwise co=
mparison matrix (step 1), culminating in the =E2=80=9Cpriority vector=E2=80=
=9D (step 3) in the final column, corresponding to the alternatives=E2=80=
=99 scores on each criterion.</p>
